# EUX-007 — CHANAKYA Live Intelligence Header (PERMANENT)

Enterprise UX Standard. Applies to every Catalyst One workspace where CHANAKYA provides operational intelligence.

## Single component

- UI: `ChanakyaLiveIntelligenceBar` in `src/components/enterprise/chanakya-live-intelligence/`
- Messages: `src/lib/chanakya-live-intelligence/` (`resolveChanakyaLiveIntelligenceWorkspace` + `buildChanakyaLiveIntelligenceMessages`)
- Do **not** create page-specific ticker implementations
- Do **not** add a second header row for intelligence

## Header order

`[ Logo / Workspace ] [ Page Controls ] [ Live Intelligence Bar ] [ Notifications ] [ Workspace Switchers ] [ CHANAKYA AI ] [ User Profile ]`

The Live Intelligence Bar fills remaining horizontal space (`flex-1 min-w-0`).

## Interaction

- Ticker is **passive** (no click-through on messages)
- Detail / Q&A / workflows open only via the **CHANAKYA AI** button
- Messages must be **contextual** to the current workspace route

## Layout integrity

- Never overlap, wrap the action cluster, or hide Notifications / AI / Profile
- Under pressure: compress ticker → scroll/truncate messages → preserve actions
- Mobile: compact CHANAKYA indicator; full feed via CHANAKYA AI
- Zero layout shift; single-line ticker

## Metrics

Reuse existing SSOT derive engines (e.g. Radar dashboard). Do not invent parallel KPI formulas for ticker copy.

## Separation from Workspace Intelligence (CO-SPRINT-112)

This header bar is **Layer 1 — Enterprise Intelligence** (organization-wide).

Do **not** reuse this component inside a Loan / Contact / Opportunity workspace ribbon.
Entity-scoped operational messages belong in `WorkspaceIntelligenceRibbon` (Layer 2) only.
See `.cursor/rules/workspace-intelligence-scope.mdc`.
